  "answer": "**The third couplet** (of eight couplets total in this poem) from Allama Iqbal's \"Anokhi waza hai, saare zamane se nirale hain\" (Bang-e-Dara Part 1, Chapter 2) reads:\n\n> O Lord, may my hope's garden thrive and gain,  \n> I fed these shoots with my own heart's blood-rain.[^1]\n\nThis is the English translation; the poem is structured as verse couplets, with each marked as a distinct paragraph in the corpus.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, Chapter 2: \"Anokhi waza hai, saare zamane se nirale hain\" (translation), [paragraph](https://falsafa-corpus.com/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/02-anokhi-waza-hai-saare-zamane-se-nirale-hain/translation/#p-61af92/).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, Chapter 2: \"Anokhi waza hai, saare zamane se nirale hain\" (translation), [chapter](https://falsafa-corpus.com/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/02-anokhi-waza-hai-saare-zamane-se-nirale-hain/translation/).",
